### Prevent Admin Panel Crawling with robots.txt

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/admin/metadata.mdx

This plain text snippet demonstrates how to create a `robots.txt` file to prevent search engines from crawling the Payload CMS Admin Panel. By adding `Disallow: /admin/`, it instructs user-agents not to access paths under the `/admin/` directory. Remember to update the `Disallow` directive if your admin panel path is customized.

```text
User-agent: *
Disallow: /admin/
```

